  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The process of weaning from mechanical ventilation was decided after clinical judgment and
      weaning predictive index. Nevertheless, indexes predicting weaning outcome like Maximal
      Inspiratory Pressure (MIP) are frequently inaccurate. However the long-term involvement of
      respiratory muscles in critically ill patients has not been established. The objective of
      this study was to assess the relationship on MIP at extubation on one-year mortality in
      critically ill patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
